Victoria is a state in south-eastern Australia. Victoria is Australia's most densely populated state and its second-most populous state overall. Most of its population lives concentrated in the area surrounding Port Phillip Bay#Comma which includes the metropolitan area of its state capital and largest city#Comma Melbourne#Comma Australia's second-largest city.

See the towering 12 Apostles#Comma get up close to native wildlife#Comma and take in iconic surf breaks#Comma pristine rainforest and misty waterfalls along the spectacular Great Ocean Road.
The City Circle Tram is a free and convenient way to see the sights of central Melbourne and the Docklands while experiencing a ride on one of the city's much loved heritage trams.

Visit Melbourne's inner-city oasis. Over 10#Comma000 plant species from around the world are presented in a kaleidoscope of color and texture. Sweeping lawns#Comma tranquil lakes and majestic trees are home to an amazing range of wildlife.

Prom Country Cheese serves cheese tastings#Comma platters and lunches featuring handmade specialty cheeses and local farm produce.
Mi Shells Seafood sell fresh#Comma locally caught seafood to the public from their families boat at Queenscliff Harbour.

Farmers Harvest is a local focused business gathering food from around the Bellarine and near by townships. They stock a wide range of seasonal fruit and vegetables concentrating on quality and flavor.
